post_text:
Football, cross country, and volleyball will resume practice as previously scheduled on Monday, August 3rd. Please contact coaches for specific details. We ask that athletes follow the protocols below prior to arriving for workouts:

1. A current physical on file with the athletic training staff.
2. Athletes MUST have a water bottle labeled with their name.
3. Athletes MUST bring their own facemasks in order to participate in summer workouts.
4. Athletes MUST bring their own snack in order to participate in summer workouts.
5. Athletes MUST bring their own towel in order to participate in summer workouts.
6. Hand sanitizer will be readily available for use by all athletes and coaches however we do RECOMMEND that each student-athlete bring their own personal bottle of hand sanitizer.

All athletes and coaches will be screened before they are allowed entry into the summer workouts for their respective sport, which includes a temperature screening and a symptom questionnaire.

post_text:
Dear Lancaster Family,

Our school district and community have suffered a tremendous loss. We are deeply saddened that Edward Jackson, a rising Lancaster High School senior and football player, has passed away following a car accident earlier today.

The loss of a young life with so much promise is always difficult, but we take comfort in knowing that his legacy will live on through the lives he touched. He will always be remembered for his positivity, determination, and commitment to succeed on and off the field.

Please keep his family, coaches, and teammates in your thoughts and prayers as we work through the pain of this devastating loss. We are providing guidance and counseling services to students, staff, and family members as needed. The well-being of our students and staff will remain a top priority as we deal with the emotions surrounding this tragedy and great loss from the Lancaster ISD family.
text:
Dear Lancaster Family,

Our school district and community have suffered a tremendous loss. We are deeply saddened that Edward Jackson, a rising Lancaster High School senior and football player, has passed away following a car accident earlier today.

The loss of a young life with so much promise is always difficult, but we take comfort in knowing that his legacy will live on through the lives he touched. He will always be remembered for his positivity, determination, and commitment to succeed on and off the field.

Please keep his family, coaches, and teammates in your thoughts and prayers as we work through the pain of this devastating loss. We are providing guidance and counseling services to students, staff, and family members as needed. The well-being of our students and staff will remain a top priority as we deal with the emotions surrounding this tragedy and great loss from the Lancaster ISD family.

post_text:
Dear Lancaster Family,

It is with profound sadness that Lancaster ISD mourns the loss of Barack and Michelle Obama Ninth Grade Center student, Roger McNeal, who tragically passed away Friday night after being struck by a car.

We are shocked and disheartened by this tragic event. Roger will always be remembered as a polite, hard-working, and respectful young man. When our school community experiences the loss of a young life with so much promise, it impacts all of us. We are providing guidance and counseling services to students, staff, and family members as needed. The well-being of our students and staff will remain a top priority as we deal with the emotions surrounding this tragedy and great loss from the Lancaster ISD family.

Please keep the family in your thoughts and prayers.

We are shocked and disheartened by this tragic event. Roger will always be remembered as a polite, hard-working, and respectful young man. When our school community experiences the loss of a young life with so much promise, it impacts all of us. post_text:
Parents, we have a few important updates regarding the remainder of the school year.
- All state assessments have been canceled for this year.
- SAT and ACT dates will be rescheduled and communicated through counselors.
- Information about AP online exam availability and IB cancelation of exams will also be communicated by counselors.
- Our campuses will receive a Not Rated: Declared State of Disaster rating for the 2019-2020 school year.

Tiger Family,
It’s almost Super Bowl Sunday, but our district got an early start with a jersey themed donuts with dad at West Main Elementary, and their young men of My Brother’s Keeper took a trip to AT&T Stadium. post_text:
It is with heavy hearts that Lancaster ISD mourns the loss of pre-K Pleasant Run Elementary School student, Nolan Coleman, who passed away Friday night in a car accident. We are heartbroken by this news.

When our school community experiences a tragedy, such as the loss of a young life, it impacts all of us. We are providing guidance and counseling services to students, staff, and family members as needed. The well-being of our students and staff will remain a top priority as we deal with the emotions surrounding this tragedy and great loss from the Lancaster ISD family.

Please keep the family in your thoughts and prayers.
